    <item>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:soundcloud,2010:tracks/292448582</guid>
      <title>President Trump's Energy Policy</title>
      <pubDate>Thu, 10 Nov 2016 21:55:24 +0000</pubDate>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TheEnergyGang/~3/w9HD60i8L7g/president-trumps-energy-policy</link>
      <itunes:duration>00:44:36</itunes:duration>
      <itunes:author>The Energy Gang</itunes:author>
      <itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit>
      <itunes:summary>Whether or not you agreed with the top-down, government-centric, executive-level strategy of the Obama Administration -- it was, arguably, America's only federal political path forward on decarbonization.

President-Elect Donald Trump plans to rip up that path as soon as he enters the White House. So how and where will he create a new one?

