Thatâs not an easy goal to achieve. The General Services Administration owns or leases more than 354 million square footage of buildings, which is enough space to fill half of Manhattan. It also manages a massive transportation fleet and must adhere to very strict cost requirements.

But the shift is happening. On this weekâs show, weâll talk with Ruth Cox, GSAâs senior sustainability officer, about how renewables and efficiency are greening government buildings while saving taxpayers money.

Weâll also have the latest on Hawaiiâs effort to both tame and encourage solar, and look at the viability of Solar Roadways. 

This podcast is brought to you by SMA, the world's leading solar inverter manufacturer.

